article.headline: N. Dakota St. 80, N.J. Tech 57
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. (AP) -- Ben Woodside scored a game-high 22 points -- one of four North Dakota State players in double figures -- as the Bison beat New Jersey Tech 80-57 on Saturday afternoon. Mike Nelson added 18 points for North Dakota State (15-7), while Andre Smith had 17 and Brett Winkelman had 15. Overall, the Bison shot 57 percent from the field and were in command for most of the game, holding several double-digit leads in the second half. Dan Stonkus led the Highlanders (4-19) with 14 points and seven rebounds, while Mike Manning scored 13 points. However, they played most of the game without leading score Clayton Barker, who sustained a knee injury less than three minutes into the game.
